    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your<strong> parsnip[s]</strong>, then peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>grated parsnip </strong>and<strong> sliced shallot </strong>to a pot with a lid with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and cook, covered, over a medium heat for an initial 25-30 min or until the parsnip has softened and the water has evaporated – this is your <strong>caramelised parsnip</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
