    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the caramelised parsnip has softened, add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>parsnip relish</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper, then separate 1 <span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>whole outer leaf </strong>per person<strong> </strong>and cut the <strong>remaining lettuce</strong> into quarters, lengthways</p>",
      "order": 6,
