    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half and add them to a baking tray, cut side up, then put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and<strong> cranberry sauce </strong>in<strong> </strong>a small bowl – this is your <strong>cranberry mayo</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>softened cranberries</strong>, then roughly chop and add them to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>cranberry vinaigrette</strong></p>",
